This paper focuses on machine learning techniques for Reading Comprehension tasks, which falls under the category of Natural Language Processing (NLP). The use of pre-trained word embeddings and representation of out-of-vocabulary tokens are common techniques in NLP, which suggests that this paper could be categorized under several sub-categories of Computer Science (CS) on arXiv. Specifically, cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are all relevant sub-categories for this paper.
